{"parse":{"title":"Lettering guide","pageid":39790668,"revid":829292713,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Standardgraph_2522_2.5%E2%80%937_mm_lettering_guides.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/61/Standardgraph_2522_2.5%E2%80%937_mm_lettering_guides.jpg/350px-Standardgraph_2522_2.5%E2%80%937_mm_lettering_guides.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"241\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/61/Standardgraph_2522_2.5%E2%80%937_mm_lettering_guides.jpg/525px-Standardgraph_2522_2.5%E2%80%937_mm_lettering_guides.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/61/Standardgraph_2522_2.5%E2%80%937_mm_lettering_guides.jpg/700px-Standardgraph_2522_2.5%E2%80%937_mm_lettering_guides.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"4628\" data-file-height=\"3181\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Standardgraph_2522_2.5%E2%80%937_mm_lettering_guides.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>2.5 to 7 millimetres (0.1 to 0.3&#160;in) lettering guides for technical drawings</div></div></div>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Pennini_da_normografo.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/24/Pennini_da_normografo.jpg/220px-Pennini_da_normografo.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"88\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/24/Pennini_da_normografo.jpg/330px-Pennini_da_normografo.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/24/Pennini_da_normografo.jpg/440px-Pennini_da_normografo.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"1611\" data-file-height=\"647\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Pennini_da_normografo.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Lettering pens for lettering guide template</div></div></div>\n<p>A <b>lettering guide template</b> is a special type of <a href=\"/wiki/Stencil\" title=\"Stencil\">template</a> used to write uniform characters. It consists of a sheet of plastic or other material with cut-outs of letters, numbers, and other shapes used especially for creating technical drawings. For decades they have been essential for lettering a <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Drawing_nameplate&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Drawing nameplate (page does not exist)\">drawing nameplate</a> so text and other designs could be made quickly and uniformly.\n</p><p>Although they have been superseded by the use of computers,  during the greater part of the last century they were used to relatively ease the lettering process in the creation of technical drawings. They were an indispensable tool for <a href=\"/wiki/Architect\" title=\"Architect\">architects</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Technical_drawing\" title=\"Technical drawing\">technical illustrators</a> in general, for labeling their drawings and plans but also for the description of projects, in which it was good practice to use a lettering template to achieve uniform and well-written text.\n</p><p>A lettering template could also be used by people <a href=\"/wiki/Illiteracy\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Illiteracy\">illiterate</a> or semi-illiterate to learn to type, or improve their handwriting.  In the course of political history some politicians, such as <a href=\"/wiki/Bettino_Craxi\" title=\"Bettino Craxi\">Bettino Craxi</a>, have used them to help people with writing difficulties. They distributed cardboard templates with the sequence of characters of their last name, so they could be easily written during the <a href=\"/wiki/Vote\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Vote\">voting</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> process.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Lettering_guide&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Graphic_design\" title=\"Graphic design\">Graphic design</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Lettering_guide&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/1992/03/20/spini-il-normografo-lecito-purche-il.html\"><i>Spini: il normografo \u00e8 lecito purch\u00e9 il voto resti segreto</i></a>. <a href=\"/wiki/La_Repubblica\" title=\"La Repubblica\">La Repubblica</a>. 20 March 1992. p.&#160;10<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">10 August</span> 2011</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Spini%3A+il+normografo+%C3%A8+lecito+purch%C3%A9+il+voto+resti+segreto&amp;rft.pages=10&amp;rft.pub=La+Repubblica&amp;rft.date=1992-03-20&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fricerca.repubblica.it%2Frepubblica%2Farchivio%2Frepubblica%2F1992%2F03%2F20%2Fspini-il-normografo-lecito-purche-il.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ALettering+guide\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span